main event: Three aircraft sighted a UFO over Iwojima, Japan, on February 21, 1960.
interesting points: The UFO was observed at an apparent altitude of 7,000 feet.
The UFO was observed for 11 minutes.
The reporting officers evaluated the sighting as a probable meteor.
A Japanese pilot initially thought the object was a missile, but the Japan Weather Bureau evaluated it as a meteor.
The incident was considered a probable natural phenomenon by the reporting officers, and no further formal report was planned.
